<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Use</h2>

  <p>
    For most raised beds, use shade cloth clips to anchor the fabric securely and add bungee cords where needed to maintain tension and handle wind. This combination gives you both stability and flexibility.
  </p>

  <p>
    Avoid relying entirely on one method, especially in variable weather conditions.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Anchor with clips, adjust with bungees.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Bottom Line</h2>

  <p>
    Shade cloth clips and bungee cords serve different roles in a raised bed setup. Clips provide structure and positioning, while bungees add flexibility and tension control.
  </p>

  <p>
    For most gardeners, using both together creates the most stable and reliable shade system.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
